    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Internal Hardware watchdog:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Aurix TC3xx supports two types of Watch dog"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Safety Watchdog (System level watchdog)",
        "CPU watchdog (Each CPU has its own watchdog)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "External Watchdog handling"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Since we have ASIL-B requirement, it is necessary to monitor Aurix using external watchdog"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "MAX20479A"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "We will not use safety Watchdog, Since External Watch dog covers the system level watchdog monitoring"
    },
    {
      "type": "image",
      "src": "https://inside-docupedia.bosch.com/confluence/download/attachments/embedded-page/CARSFW/SM06%20SCC%20Watchdog/SM7%20SCC%20Watchdog.bmp?api=v2",
      "alt": "",
      "local_path": "_images/SM06 SCC Watchdog/SM7 SCC Watchdog.bmp"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Startup operation:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "CPU0 Watchdog are active immediately after Reset/PowerOn."
    }
